        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"306601\">@Kyle Miller</span> is it possible that this syntax declaration is slightly wrong?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">syntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">valConfigItem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atomic</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\" (\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">notFollowedBy</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"s2\">\"discharger\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"s2\">\"disch\"</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ident</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"s2\">\"config\"</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" := \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">withoutPosition</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\")\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>With <code>ident &lt;|&gt; &amp;\"config\"</code>, I would expect that <code>ident</code> overlaps <code>&amp;\"config\"</code>, and hence that the second alternative is never considered.</p>",
